# GPS Location Tracking & Geo-Fencing Implementation Plan

## Scope Summary

Implementing location-related features across the AryanVeda DMS system:

### 1. GPS Coordinates in Attendance Marking
- Add `latitude`, `longitude`, `locationAddress` to attendance model/types
- Capture GPS on attendance mark (frontend geolocation API)
- Store coordinates in backend
- Display location link in attendance history

### 2. GPS Coordinates in Beat Visits (I Am Here = Beat Visit rename)
- Add `latitude`, `longitude`, `locationAddress` to retailer visit model
- Capture GPS during beat visit creation
- Display location in visit history

### 3. GPS Location Tracking Module (New)
- **Backend**: New `location` module (model, controller, service, routes)
- **Frontend**: New `location.service.ts`, GPS tracking page, team map view
- Periodic GPS track submission for SO/ASM/RSM
- Manager view for tracking team locations

### 4. Geo-Fencing
- Define territory boundaries (center point + radius)
- Outstation detection for attendance
- Alert when user marks attendance outside assigned territory

